com.rli.util.identityData

Class ComplexValue

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.rli.util.identityData.ComplexValue
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable

    public class ComplexValue
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Cloneable
    A complex value represents a value that is itself composed of a set of attributes and values. For example, a complex value for a "name" attribute could be: { "first":"John", "middle":"Patrick", "last": Smith }.

      • withAttribute

        public ComplexValue withAttribute(java.lang.String attributeName,
                                  java.lang.String value)
        Returns an instance of the current ComplexValue object with the specified attribute set to the specified value. This method is intended to be used as a builder to easily set attributes on a ComplexValue object.

        Example: ComplexValue cv = new ComplexValue().withAttribute("city", "Novato").withAttribute("name", "Radiant Logic");

        Parameters:
        attributeName - The name of an attribute.
        value - The value to set for the attribute.
        Returns:
        An instance of the current ComplexValue object with the specified attribute set to the specified value.

      • withAttribute

        public ComplexValue withAttribute(java.lang.String attributeName,
                                  java.util.List<java.lang.String> values)
        Returns an instance of the current ComplexValue object with the specified attribute set to the specified values. This method is intended to be used as a builder to easily set attributes on a ComplexValue object.

        Example: ComplexValue cv = new ComplexValue().withAttribute("city", Arrays.asList("Novato", "Chicago")) .withAttribute("name", "Radiant Logic");

        Parameters:
        attributeName - The name of an attribute.
        values - The values to set for the attribute.
        Returns:
        An instance of the current ComplexValue object with the specified attribute set to the specified values.
